            "subject": "LU-7848 target: Do not fail MDT-MDT connection"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Doug Oucharek",
          "email": "doug.s.oucharek@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-04-15 18:37:54.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-05-31 04:54:21.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-8022 lnet: Don't access NULL NI on failure path",
        "message": "LU-8022 lnet: Don't access NULL NI on failure path\n\nIn kiblnd_passive_connect(), if we are failing the connection\nattempt because we cannot find a valid NI (we have a NULL NI),\nwe were coring after the \"goto fail\" because the failure\npath was assuming non-NULL NI.\n\nThis patch ensures we don't dereference a NULL NI on that\nfailure path.\n\nSigned-off-by: Doug Oucharek <doug.s.oucharek@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I4f3deb78b4d3e9d81551ba915ceee852ec3b0792\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/19614\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Matt Ezell <ezellma@ornl.gov>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
